sql:
SELECT MAX(net_pay) AS highest_net_pay, employee_id
FROM payroll
WHERE payment_date = (
  SELECT MAX(payment_date) FROM payroll
);

SELECT total_earnings, total_deductions
FROM compensation_summary
WHERE summary_date = '2023-04-15';

SELECT current_amount 
FROM earnings
WHERE effective_date = (SELECT MAX(effective_date) FROM earnings);

external_knowledge:
Take-home pay refers to the amount of money an employee actually receives after deductions and taxes have been taken out of their salary; 
Net pay is the amount of money an employee receives after deductions have been taken out of their salary, but before taxes. 
Annual benefits and taxes are calculated by multiplying the monthly amounts by 12.

sql:
SELECT SUM(net_pay) AS total_net_pay
FROM payroll
WHERE net_pay < (
  SELECT AVG(net_pay) 
  FROM payroll
);
